Privacy Policy for RealWorth

Last updated: July 19, 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how RealWorth (“we,” “our,” or “us”) collects, uses, and protects information when you use the RealWorth mobile application (the “App”).

RealWorth is a mobile application that helps users compare the real value of products across countries using currency conversion, purchasing power parity (PPP), and cost of living data.

By using the App, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

1. Information We Collect

We aim to collect only the information needed to operate and improve the App.

a. Information stored on your device The App may store preferences locally on your device, such as:

Language preference
Theme / appearance settings
Other app settings you choose
This information is stored using local device storage and is not used to identify you personally.

b. Information collected automatically When you use the App, certain technical information may be collected automatically, including:

Device type and operating system
App usage data related to ads and performance
Internet connection status (required to fetch exchange rate data)
c. Information we do not collect We do not require you to create an account. We do not knowingly collect names, email addresses, phone numbers, payment details, or precise location data for our own purposes.

2. How We Use Information

We use collected information to:

Provide currency conversion and country comparison features
Retrieve up-to-date exchange rate data from third-party APIs
Save your in-app preferences
Display advertisements
Improve App performance, stability, and user experience
Maintain security and prevent misuse
3. Advertising

The App uses Google AdMob to display ads.

Google AdMob and its partners may collect and process information such as:

Advertising ID / device identifiers
IP address
Device and app interaction data
Approximate location derived from IP address
This information may be used to show personalized or non-personalized ads, measure ad performance, and prevent fraud.

For more information, please review Google’s privacy policy:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

You may also manage ad preferences through your device settings (for example, reset advertising ID or limit ad tracking, depending on your platform).

4. Third-Party Services

The App may communicate with third-party services, including:

Currency / exchange rate data providers
Google AdMob
These third parties may process data according to their own privacy policies. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of third-party services.

5. Data Storage and Security

App preferences are stored locally on your device. We take reasonable measures to protect information processed through the App. However, no method of electronic transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. Data Retention

Local preference data remains on your device until you clear the App data or uninstall the App. Advertising-related data processed by Google AdMob is retained according to Google’s policies.

7. Children’s Privacy

The App is not directed to children under the age of 13 (or the equivalent minimum age in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided personal information through the App, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.

8. Your Rights and Choices

Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal data, such as access, correction, deletion, or restriction of processing.

You can:

Change language and theme settings in the App
Clear App data from your device settings
Uninstall the App at any time
Manage advertising preferences through your device or Google account settings
If you have questions about your privacy rights, contact us using the details below.

9. International Users

If you use the App from outside the country where our services are operated, your information may be processed in other countries where third-party providers (such as Google) maintain servers.

10. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected by updating the “Last updated” date. Continued use of the App after changes means you accept the revised policy.
